CentOS 7 Filesystem Hierarchy:

It is inverted tree structer like branches, then sub branches. The same Hierarchy inherited in Linux/Unix file system
Every thing is distrubuted, everything is cattered and stored in one particuar location. and it's just like a distributed file system.
 / ---> root of the file system or top level directory or starting file of the directory. under root, we have multiple sub or child directories which are mentioned below.


boot - 
etc - user database & system configuration files will be saved in this directory 
proc - process related like dynamic process informantion
dev - hardware related information
home - all regular user will be having hoe directory 
root - 
var - 
usr - 
run - 
tmp - 
mnt - 
opt - 
